TTP header. I need to build a request with ObjectOutputStream, ensuring to handle responses robustly and assert specific outputs. Overall, I've got to ensure clarity and handle failures smartly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Handling exportObject generation**\\n\\nI need to generate exportObject stubs that create proxy methods for all public methods, including `EchoService.echo(Object)`. It’s using the toCtClass parameters and returning correctly. I’m considering if `exportObject(\\\"echo-service\\\", service);` will cover line 114. Also, lookupName might not be active, so I want to ensure I manage that situation with a try/finally for server.end. I’ll look into how AppletServer binds and potential issues with the ServerSocket and translator in the native image context.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fSgsunDvk6YWZjZXUZuOQQDy|fc_0061eea50b702b760169f9e0e35228819fbedebaa934cdbb38", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/AppletServerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage javassist.javassist;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\nimport javassist.tools.rmi.AppletServer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class AppletServerTest {\n    private static final int METHOD_SEARCH_LIMIT = 128;\n\n    @Test\n    void exportedObjectCanReceiveSerializedRmiInvocationAndReturnSerializedValue() throws Exception {\n        AppletServer server = new AppletServer(0);\n        try {\n            int objectId = server.exportObject(\"echo-service\", new EchoService());\n            Object echoResult = null;\n\n            for (int methodId = 0; methodId < METHOD_SEARCH_LIMIT && echoResult == null; methodId++) {\n                Response response = invokeMethod(server, objectId, methodId, \"argument\");\n                if (response.success && \"echo:argument\".equals(response.value)) {\n                    echoResult = response.value;\n                }\n            }\n\n            assertThat(echoResult).isEqualTo(\"echo:argument\");\n        } finally {\n            server.end();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class EchoService {\n        public String echo(Object value) {\n            return \"echo:\" + value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Response invokeMethod(AppletServer server, int objectId, int methodId, Object argument) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream requestBytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream request = new ObjectOutputStream(requestBytes)) {\n            request.writeInt(objectId);\n            request.writeInt(methodId);\n            request.writeInt(1);\n            request.writeObject(argument);\n        }\n\n        ByteArrayOutputStream responseBytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        server.doReply(new ByteArrayInputStream(requestBytes.toByteArray()), responseBytes, \"POST /rmi HTTP/1.0\");\n        return readResponse(responseBytes.toByteArray());\n    }\n\n    private static Response readResponse(byte[] bytes) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\n        ByteArrayInputStream input = new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes);\n        skipHttpHeader(input);\n        try (ObjectInputStream response = new ObjectInputStream(input)) {\n            boolean success = response.readBoolean();\n            if (success) {\n                return new Response(true, response.readObject());\n            }\n            return new Response(false, response.readUTF());\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void skipHttpHeader(ByteArrayInputStream input) throws IOException {\n        byte[] expectedHeader = \"HTTP/1.0 200 OK\\r\\n\\r\\n\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII);\n        byte[] actualHeader = input.readNBytes(expectedHeader.length);\n\n        assertThat(actualHeader).containsExactly(expectedHeader);\n    }\n\n    private static final class Response {\n        private final boolean success;\n        private final Object value;\n\n        private Response(boolean success, Object value) {\n            this.success = success;\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 736, "output": 1876, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24116, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777983696466, "responseId": "resp_0061eea50b702b760169f9e0d136ac819fb6a11fefcafda5f0"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_fSgsunDvk6YWZjZXUZuOQQDy|fc_0061eea50b702b760169f9e0e35228819fbedebaa934cdbb38", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3396 bytes to tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/AppletServerTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777983720851}]}
